---
// Acknowledgement banner. Above the fold, above the nav. The first
// paragraph names the paper before anything else on the page; the
// demo follows below.
---

<header class="border-b hairline bg-[var(--color-page-dark)]">
  <div class="container-wide pt-14 pb-12 md:pt-20 md:pb-16">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-5">A companion site to a reimplementation of IncPy</p>
    <h1 class="h-display max-w-[26ch]">
      Edit one line in a multi-step Python script. Save. Rerun in seconds, not minutes.
    </h1>
    <p class="lede mt-6">
      <code>rote</code> is a pure-Python library that watches a script as it runs, finds the
      function calls that are slow and safe to remember, and persists their results so the
      next run skips the work that didn't change. It's a reimplementation of <em>IncPy</em>
      (Guo &amp; Engler, ISSTA 2011); the design is theirs, the platform underneath is what's
      new. This page is the comparison.
    </p>
  </div>
</header>
